== What we do for you ==

(% class="box infomessage" %)
(((
**FactHarbor analyzes claims and articles** by breaking them into verifiable pieces, collecting supporting and opposing evidence from web sources and databases, and evaluating evidence quality and source reliability across evidence-defined analysis boundaries. It compares, challenges, and reconciles findings through a structured multi-agent AI debate process. **It delivers a transparent verdict where every conclusion links to cited evidence, so you can judge for yourself.**
)))
== Where FactHarbor stands out ==

FactHarbor runs an end-to-end automated verdict pipeline on real claims and is the only end-to-end **multi-agent debate** system for fact-checking with live evidence retrieval. While research implementations exist (ED2D, MADR), FactHarbor is unique as a user-facing service. It uses evidence-defined analysis boundaries, structured advocate/challenger/reconciler roles, cross-provider model routing (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Mistral), and evidence-weighted contestation rules so unsupported objections do not change verdicts. Each verdict is auditable: you can see the cited evidence, source-quality weighting, and which evidence-backed challenges changed the outcome.


